This modification is dependent on 
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/72455
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/72454
It is for determining the current status of the slot when performing slot hot service.

Since the Thermal team stated on August 6th that there will be no Air blocker in the data center in the future, the changes made in https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/72454
and https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/72455
to determine the presence of an Air blocker are no longer needed. 

Instead, it is sufficient to determine if the Sentinel Dome is inserted into the slot based on the Fru object under the Entity manager
Why are we stopping the fan control service??

Because I don't want the fan speed to be readjusted by the phosphor-pid-control's auto mode after I adjust the fan duty.

Or is it that I don't actually need to stop the phosphor-pid control?
I just need to use `busctl` to set the `Manual` property under `/xyz/openbmc_project/settings/fanctrl/zone0` to `true`, then adjust the fan duty. 
When I need to return to auto mode, I can set the `Manual` property back to `false`?
Yes, please use manual mode if that's what you need.
You cannot make calls to a facebook/openbmc tool in the open source code.

How about using `busctl` to set the `Target` property of the `xyz.openbmc_project.FanSensor` object under the `xyz.openbmc_project.FanSensor` service to the corresponding value to adjust the fan speed?
Is this method correct?

Thank you for your suggestion.
Yes.
